__glossary-link" data-tooltip-content="#ingredients-glossary--3 &gt; article" data-tooltip-width="350" data-tooltip-hide-delay="200" data-tooltip-flyout="true">pasta</a> shapes<span class="ingredients-list__glossary-element" id="ingredients-glossary--3"><article id="node-5973541" role="main" class="node node-glossary-item node-teaser node-teaser clearfix main row grid-padding"><div class="node-image"> <a href="/glossary/pasta"><img src="//www.bbcgoodfood.com/sites/default/files/styles/bbcgf_thumbnail_search/public/glossary-item/glossary-image/2016/07/pasta.png?itok=whXD7ulw" width="100" height="100" alt="Pasta" title="Pasta" /></a></div><h2 class="node-title node-glossary-title"><a href="/glossary/pasta">Pasta</a></h2> <span class="fonetic text-style-alt">pah-stah</span><p>Pasta is the Italian name for Italy's version of a basic foodstuff which is made in manyâ€¦</p> </article></span></li><li class="ingredients-list__item" itemprop="ingredients" content="300g baby spinachleaves">300g baby spinach leaves</li><li class="ingredients-list__item" itemprop="ingredients" content="6 tbsp ricotta">6 tbsp <a href="/glossary/ricotta" class="ingredients-list__glossary-link" data-tooltip-content="#ingredients-glossary--4 &gt; article" data-tooltip-width="350" data-tooltip-hide-delay="200" data-tooltip-flyout="true">ricotta</a><span class="ingredients-list__glossary-element" id="ingredients-glossary--4"><article id="node-259981" role="main" class="node node-glossary-item node-teaser node-teaser clearfix main row grid-padding"><div class="node-image"> <a href="/glossary/ricotta"><img src="//www.bbcgoodfood.com/sites/default/files/styles/bbcgf_thumbnail_search/public/glossary/ricotta.jpg?itok=LqeprARk" width="100" height="100" alt="Ricotta" title="Ricotta is an Italian curd cheese made from whey" /></a></div><h2 class="node-title node-glossary-title"><a href="/glossary/ricotta">Ricotta</a></h2> <span class="fonetic text-style-alt">ree-cot-a</span><p>Ricotta is an ItalianÂ cheese made from whey andÂ traditionallyÂ a by-product ofâ€¦</p> </article></span></li><li class="ingredients-list__item" itemprop="ingredients" content="4 sageleaves, very finely chopped">4 <a href="/glossary/sage" class="ingredients-list__glossary-link" data-tooltip-content="#ingredients-glossary--5 &gt; article" data-tooltip-width="350" data-tooltip-hide-delay="200" data-tooltip-flyout="true">sage</a> leaves, very finely chopped<span class="ingredients-list__glossary-element" id="ingredients-glossary--5"><article id="node-260171" role="main" class="node node-glossary-item node-teaser node-teaser clearfix main row grid-padding"><div class="node-image"> <a href="/glossary/sage"><img src="//www.bbcgoodfood.com/sites/default/files/styles/bbcgf_thumbnail_search/public/glossary/sage-cropped.jpg?itok=dHFYO9J_" width="100" height="100" alt="Sage" title="Sage" /></a></div><h2 class="node-title node-glossary-title"><a href="/glossary/sage">Sage</a></h2> <span class="fonetic text-style-alt">sa-age</span><p>Popular in both Italian and British cookery, sage has long, grey-green leaves with a slightlyâ€¦</p> </article></span></li><li class="ingredients-list__item" itemprop="ingredients" content="zest and juice 1 lemon">zest and juice 1 <a href="/glossary/lemon" class="ingredients-list__glossary-link" data-tooltip-content="#ingredients-glossary--6 &gt; article" data-tooltip-width="350" data-tooltip-hide-delay="200" data-tooltip-flyout="true">lemon</a><span class="ingredients-list__glossary-element" id="ingredients-glossary--6"><article id="node-259661" role="main" class="node node-glossary-item node-teaser node-teaser clearfix main row grid-padding"><div class="node-image"> <a href="/glossary/lemon"><img src="//www.bbcgoodfood.com/sites/default/files/styles/bbcgf_thumbnail_search/public/glossary/lemon.jpg?itok=fstxl0E6" width="100" height="100" alt="Lemon" title="Lemons are one of the most versatile fruits around, and contain a high level of Vitamin C" /></a></div><h2 class="node-title node-glossary-title"><a href="/glossary/lemon">Lemon</a></h2> <span class="fonetic text-style-alt">le-mon</span><p>Oval in shape, with a pronouced bulge on one end, lemons are one of the most versatile fruitsâ€¦</p> </article></span></li><li class="ingredients-list__item" itemprop="ingredients" content="a few gratings of fresh nutmeg">a few gratings of fresh <a href="/glossary/nutmeg" class="ingredients-list__glossary-link" data-tooltip-content="#ingredients-glossary--7 &gt; article" data-tooltip-width="350" data-tooltip-hide-delay="200" data-tooltip-flyout="true">nutmeg</a><span class="ingredients-list__glossary-element" id="ingredients-glossary--7"><article id="node-6458441" role="main" class="node node-glossary-item node-teaser node-teaser clearfix main row grid-padding"><div class="node-image"> <a href="/glossary/nutmeg"><img src="//www.bbcgoodfood.com/sites/default/files/styles/bbcgf_thumbnail_search/public/glossary-item/glossary-image/2017/03/nutmeg_700.jpg?itok=tuPKYNYY" width="100" height="100" alt="Nutmeg" title="Nutmeg" /></a></div><h2 class="node-title node-glossary-title"><a href="/glossary/nutmeg">Nutmeg</a></h2> <span class="fonetic text-style-alt">nut-meg</span><p><span style="line-height:107%">One of the most useful of spices for both sweet and savoury</span>â€¦</p> </article></span></li></ul></div></div> </section> <section id="recipe-method" class="responsive-tabs__pane"><h2 class="responsive-tabs__pane-title">Method</h2><div class="method"><ol class="method__list"><li class="method__item" itemprop="recipeInstructions"><p>Heat oven to 200C/180C fan/gas 6. Tip the squash and shallots into a large roasting dish. Toss in the oil, season and roast for 40 mins, stirring once.</p></li><li class="method__item" itemprop="recipeInstructions"><p>Meanwhile, cook the pasta following pack instructions, reserving a few tbsp of cooking water. Place the spinach in a large colander and pour over boiling water to wilt. Allow to cool a little, then squeeze out as much excess water as possible. Pop into a bowl with two-thirds of the ricotta, the sage, lemon juice and zest, nutmeg and seasoning, then stir.</p></li><li class="method__item" itemprop="recipeInstructions"><p>Next, tip the ricotta mixture into the hot drained pasta. Stir, adding a few tbsp of the cooking liquid. Mix most of the roasted veg with the pasta. Divide into bowls and dot with the remaining ricotta and scatter over any final bits of veg.</p></li></ol></div> <footer class="recipe-info"><div class="recipe-info__publication">Recipe from Good Food magazine, <a href="/search/recipes/date/1393632000" class="text-style-alt">March 2014</a></div> <a class="recipe-info__magazine-ad" href=" https://www.buysubscriptions.com/print/bbc-good-food-magazine-subscription?promo=GFBS718&style=Brand&utm_medium=brandsite&utm_source=bbcgoodfood.com&utm_campaign=recipe_GFBS718_Brand&utm_content=recipe-banner" rel="external" onclick="Drupal.GFAnalytics.trackEvent(['Magazines', 'subscribe', 'Recipe' ])"> <img src="https://www.bbcgoodfood.com/sites/default/files/magazine/gf_aug18_337x109.jpg" alt="BBC GoodFood Magazine" /> </a> </footer> </section></div></div> <section id="block-bbcgf-search-views-bbcgf-cc-rel-recipes" class="section-box section-box--you-may-also-like"> <header class="section-box__header"><h2 class="section-box__title">You may also like</h2> </header><div class="section-box__content"><div class="carousel"><div class="flexslider type-1" data-type="1"><ul class="slides"><li class=""><article id="node-6880636" class="node node-recipe node-carousel-slide-narrow clearfix"><div class="vertical-push-item__image"> <img src="//www.bbcgoodfood.com/sites/default/files/styles/carousel_small/public/recipe/recipe-image/2017/10/butternut-sage-hazelnut-quiche.jpg?itok=j8j1fG5X" width="324" height="294" alt="A gold plate serving a butternut, sage &amp; hazelnut quiche" title="Butternut, sage &amp; hazelnut quiche" /></div><h3 class="vertical-push-item__title"> <a href="/recipes/buttern